In [162]:
# Dcodage des modalits
Status_of_existing_checking_account = {"A11" : "... <    0 DM",
                                       "A12" : "0 <= ... <  200 DM",
                                       "A13" : "... >= 200 DM / salary assignments for at least 1 year",
                                       "A14" : "no checking account"}
df["Status of existing checking account"] = df["Status of existing checking account"].map(Status_of_existing_checking_account)

Credit_history={"A30" : "no credits taken / all credits paid back duly",
                "A31" : "all credits at this bank paid back duly",
                "A32" : "existing credits paid back duly till now",
                "A33" : "delay in paying off in the past",
                "A34" : "critical account / other credits existing (not at this bank)"}
df["Credit history"] = df["Credit history"].map(Credit_history)

Purpose={"A40" : "car (new)",
         "A41" : "car (used)",
         "A42" : "furniture/equipment",
         "A43" : "radio/television",
         "A44" : "domestic appliances",
         "A45" : "repairs",
         "A46" : "education",
         "A47" : "(vacation - does not exist?)",
         "A48" : "retraining",
         "A49" : "business",
         "A410" : "others"}
df["Purpose"]=df["Purpose"].map(Purpose)

Savings_account_bonds={"A61" : "... <  100 DM",
                       "A62" : "100 <= ... <  500 DM",
                       "A63" : "500 <= ... < 1000 DM",
                       "A64" : ".. >= 1000 DM",
                       "A65" : "unknown/ no savings account"}
df["Savings account/bonds"]=df["Savings account/bonds"].map(Savings_account_bonds)

Present_employment_since={"A71" : "unemployed",
                          "A72" : "... < 1 year",
                          "A73" : "1  <= ... < 4 years",
                          "A74" : "4  <= ... < 7 years",
                          "A75" : ".. >= 7 years"}
df["Present employment since"]=df["Present employment since"].map(Present_employment_since)

Personal_status_and_sex={"A91" : "male:divorced/separated",
                         "A92" : "female:divorced/separated/married",
                         "A93" : "male:single",
                         "A94" : "male:married/widowed",
                         "A95" : "female:single"}
df["Personal status and sex"]=df["Personal status and sex"].map(Personal_status_and_sex)

Other_debtors_guarantors={"A101" : "none",
                          "A102" : "co-applicant",
                          "A103" : "guarantor"}
df["Other debtors / guarantors"]=df["Other debtors / guarantors"].map(Other_debtors_guarantors)

Property={"A121" : "real estate",
          "A122" : "building society savings agreement / life insurance",
          "A123" : "car or other",
          "A124" : "unknown / no property"}
df["Property"]=df["Property"].map(Property)

Other_installment_plans={"A141" : "bank",
                         "A142" : "stores",
                         "A143" : "none"}
df["Other installment plans"]=df["Other installment plans"].map(Other_installment_plans)

Housing={"A151" : "rent",
         "A152" : "own",
         "A153" : "for free"}
df["Housing"]=df["Housing"].map(Housing)

Job={"A171" : "unemployed/ unskilled  - non-resident",
     "A172" : "unskilled - resident",
     "A173" : "skilled employee / official",
     "A174" : "management/ self-employed/highly qualified employee/ officer"}
df["Job"]=df["Job"].map(Job)

Telephone={"A191" : "none",
           "A192" : "yes, registered under the customers name"}
df["Telephone"]=df["Telephone"].map(Telephone)

foreign_worker={"A201" : "yes",
                "A202" : "no"}
df["foreign worker"]=df["foreign worker"].map(foreign_worker)

#Risk={1:"Good Risk",
#      2:"Bad Risk"}
#df["Risk"]=df["Risk"].map(Risk)
df.Risk.replace([1,2], [1,0], inplace=True)

mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True


f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (11, 9))

cmap = sns.diverging_palette(220, 10, as_cmap = True)

# Dans la documentation:
# "It is worse to class a customer as good when they are bad (5), 
# than it is to class a customer as bad when they are good (1)."

# Cela signifie que le modle qu'on va utiliser doit retourner un nombre tres faible de faux positive
# il faut donc que FP ~ 0

# On a : =/(+)
# On sintressera donc  la prcision, cest--dire la proportion de prdictions correctes parmi les individus que lon a prdits positifs.
# Une prcision leve nous indique que la pluplard des exemple prdis positive, le sont effectivement.
# Il faut donc que la precision soit la plus leve possible
# scoring = "precision"

# On va utiliser 6 modeles, visualiser la performance de chacun  partir du graphe de la courbe ROC et comparer les scores donns par les prcisions

k-NN¶

In [214]:
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn import metrics
error = []
# on calcule d'erreur pour k entre 40 et 80 
# on calcule pour chaque itration, l'erreur moyenne pour les valeurs prdites de l'ensemble de test est calcule et sauvegarde ds la liste erreur.
for i in range(40, 80):
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(i)
    knn_model = knn.fit(X_train, y_train)
    pred_i = knn_model.predict(X_test)
    error.append(np.mean(pred_i != y_test))
    
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(range(40, 80), error, color='red', linestyle='dashed', marker='o',
         markerfacecolor='blue', markersize=10)
plt.title('Taux Erreur pour les differentes valeurs de k')
plt.xlabel('K ')
plt.ylabel('Erreur')
Out[214]:
Text(0, 0.5, 'Erreur')

# On applique maintenent le kNN pour le meilleur k
knn = KNeighborsClassifier(43)
knn_model = knn.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred_knn =knn_model.predict(X_test)
np.mean(y_pred_knn != y_test)

print('Accuracy of K-NN Classifier on training set: {:.2f}'
     .format(knn.score(X_train, y_train)))
print('Accuracy of K-NN Classifier on test set: {:.2f}'
     .format(knn.score(X_test, y_test)))

print("\nConfusion Matrix:")
print(metrics.confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_knn))
print(metrics.classification_report(y_test, y_pred_knn))
print('Precision of K-NN Classifier: {:.3f}'
     .format(metrics.precision_score(y_test, y_pred_knn)))
precisions.append(metrics.precision_score(y_test, y_pred_knn))
